  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n    <title>Big-Theta Notation Explorer</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: monospace;\n            max-width: 900px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n            line-height: 1.6;\n        }\n        .container {\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n            padding: 10px;\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n        }\n        .control-panel {\n            display: flex;\n            flex-wrap: wrap;\n            gap: 10px;\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n        }\n        .graph-container {\n            height: 300px;\n            border: 1px solid #000;\n            position: relative;\n            margin-top: 20px;\n        }\n        .line {\n            position: absolute;\n            height: 2px;\n            background-color: black;\n            transform-origin: 0 0;\n        }\n        .point {\n            position: absolute;\n            width: 4px;\n            height: 4px;\n            background-color: black;\n            border-radius: 50%;\n        }\n        table {\n            border-collapse: collapse;\n            width: 100%;\n            margin-top: 20px;\n        }\n        th, td {\n            border: 1px solid #000;\n            padding: 5px;\n            text-align: left;\n        }\n        input[type=\"range\"] {\n            width: 200px;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Big-Theta (Θ) Notation Explorer</h1>\n    \n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h2>Concept Explanation</h2>\n        <p>Big-Theta (Θ) describes an asymptotic tight bound on the growth rate of a function. A function f(n) is Θ(g(n)) if there exist positive constants c₁, c₂, and n₀ such that:</p>\n        <p>0 ≤ c₁·g(n) ≤ f(n) ≤ c₂·g(n) for all n ≥ n₀</p>\n        <p>This means f(n) grows at the same rate as g(n) within constant factors.</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h2>Interactive Proof</h2>\n        <div class=\"control-panel\">\n            <div>\n                <label>f(n): \n                    <select id=\"function-select\">\n                        <option value=\"n\">n</option>\n                        <option value=\"n^2\">n²</option>\n                        <option value=\"n^3\">n³</option>\n                        <option value=\"log n\">log n</option>\n                        <option value=\"n log n\">n log n</option>\n                        <option value=\"2^n\">2ⁿ</option>\n                    </select>\n                </label>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n                <label>c₁: <input type=\"range\" id=\"c1-slider\" min=\"0.1\" max=\"2\" step=\"0.1\" value=\"1\"></label>\n                <span id=\"c1-value\">1</span>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n                <label>c₂: <input type=\"range\" id=\"c2-slider\" min=\"1\" max=\"5\" step=\"0.1\" value=\"2\"></label>\n                <span id=\"c2-value\">2</span>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n                <label>n₀: <input type=\"range\" id=\"n0-slider\" min=\"1\" max=\"20\" step=\"1\" value=\"5\"></label>\n                <span id=\"n0-value\">5</span>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n                <button id=\"auto-adjust-btn\">Auto-Adjust Constants</button>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div class=\"graph-container\" id=\"proof-graph\"></div>\n        \n        <div id=\"proof-result\"></div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h2>Function Comparison</h2>\n        <div class=\"control-panel\">\n            <div>\n                <label>Function 1: \n                    <select id=\"compare-f1\">\n                        <option value=\"n\">n</option>\n                        <option value=\"n^2\" selected>n²</option>\n                        <option value=\"n^3\">n³</option>\n                        <option value=\"log n\">log n</option>\n                        <option value=\"n log n\">n log n</option>\n                    </select>\n                </label>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n                <label>Function 2: \n                    <select id=\"compare-f2\">\n                        <option value=\"n\">n</option>\n                        <option value=\"n^2\">n²</option>\n                        <option value=\"n^3\">n³</option>\n                        <option value=\"log n\" selected>log n</option>\n                        <option value=\"n log n\">n log n</option>\n                    </select>\n                </label>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n                <label>Max n: <input type=\"range\" id=\"compare-max-n\" min=\"10\" max=\"1000\" step=\"10\" value=\"100\"></label>\n                <span id=\"compare-max-n-value\">100</span>\n            </div>\n            <button id=\"compare-btn\">Compare</button>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div class=\"graph-container\" id=\"compare-graph\"></div>\n        \n        <div id=\"comparison-result\"></div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h2>Algorithm Analysis</h2>\n        <div class=\"control-panel\">\n            <div>\n                <label>Algorithm: \n                    <select id=\"algorithm-select\">\n                        <option value=\"linear-search\">Linear Search</option>\n                        <option value=\"binary-search\">Binary Search</option>\n                        <option value=\"bubble-sort\">Bubble Sort</option>\n                        <option value=\"merge-sort\">Merge Sort</option>\n                        <option value=\"quick-sort\">Quick Sort (avg)</option>\n                        <option value=\"fibonacci-recursive\">Fibonacci (recursive)</option>\n                    </select>\n                </label>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n                <label>Input Size (n): <input type=\"range\" id=\"algorithm-n\" min=\"1\" max=\"50\" step=\"1\" value=\"10\"></label>\n                <span id=\"algorithm-n-value\">10</span>\n            </div>\n            <button id=\"analyze-btn\">Analyze</button>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div id=\"algorithm-result\">\n            <table>\n                <tr>\n                    <th>Time Complexity</th>\n                    <th>Big-Θ</th>\n                    <th>Explanation</th>\n                </tr>\n            </table>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h2>Big-Theta Tester</h2>\n        <p>Enter your own functions to test if f(n) = Θ(g(n)):</p>\n        <div class=\"control-panel\">\n            <div>\n                <label>f(n): <input type=\"text\" id=\"custom-f\" value=\"3n^2 + 2n + 1\"></label>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n                <label>g(n): <input type=\"text\" id=\"custom-g\" value=\"n^2\"></label>\n            </div>\n            <button id=\"test-btn\">Test</button>\n        </div>\n        <div id=\"test-result\"></div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <script>\n        // Helper functions\n        function evaluateFunction(expr, n) {\n            expr = expr.replace(/\\^/g, '**').replace(/log n/g, `Math.log(${n})`);\n            try {\n                return eval(expr.replace(/n/g, n));\n            } catch {\n                return NaN;\n            }\n        }\n        \n        function getFunctionName(expr) {\n            const map = {\n                'n': 'n',\n                'n**2': 'n²',\n                'n^2': 'n²',\n                'n**3': 'n³',\n                'n^3': 'n³',\n                'Math.log(n)': 'log n',\n                'log n': 'log n',\n                'n*Math.log(n)': 'n log n',\n                'n log n': 'n log n',\n                '2**n': '2ⁿ',\n                '2^n': '2ⁿ'\n            };\n            return map[expr] || expr;\n        }\n        \n        // Proof section\n        const functionSelect = document.getElementById('function-select');\n        const c1Slider = document.getElementById('c1-slider');\n        const c2Slider = document.getElementById('c2-slider');\n        const n0Slider = document.getElementById('n0-slider');\n        const c1Value = document.getElementById('c1-value');\n        const c2Value = document.getElementById('c2-value');\n        const n0Value = document.getElementById('n0-value');\n        const autoAdjustBtn = document.getElementById('auto-adjust-btn');\n        const proofGraph = document.getElementById('proof-graph');\n        const proofResult = document.getElementById('proof-result');\n        \n        function updateProof() {\n            const fExpr = functionSelect.value;\n            const c1 = parseFloat(c1Slider.value);\n            const c2 = parseFloat(c2Slider.value);\n            const n0 = parseInt(n0Slider.value);\n            \n            c1Value.textContent = c1;\n            c2Value.textContent = c2;\n            n0Value.textContent = n0;\n            \n            // Clear previous graph\n            proofGraph.innerHTML = '';\n            \n            // Calculate points\n            const maxN = Math.max(20, n0 * 2);\n            const points = [];\n            const lowerPoints = [];\n            const upperPoints = [];\n            \n            for (let n = 1; n <= maxN; n++) {\n                const x = (n / maxN) * proofGraph.clientWidth;\n                const y = proofGraph.clientHeight - (evaluateFunction(fExpr, n) / evaluateFunction(fExpr, maxN)) * proofGraph.clientHeight;\n                points.push({x, y, n});\n                \n                const lowerY = proofGraph.clientHeight - (c1 * evaluateFunction(fExpr, n) / evaluateFunction(fExpr, maxN)) * proofGraph.clientHeight;\n                lowerPoints.push({x, y: lowerY, n});\n                \n                const upperY = proofGraph.clientHeight - (c2 * evaluateFunction(fExpr, n) / evaluateFunction(fExpr, maxN)) * proofGraph.clientHeight;\n                upperPoints.push({x, y: upperY, n});\n            }\n            \n            // Draw lines\n            for (let i = 0; i < points.length - 1; i++) {\n                // f(n) line\n                const line = document.createElement('div');\n                line.className = 'line';\n                line.style.left = points[i].x + 'px';\n                line.style.top = points[i].y + 'px';\n                line.style.width = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(points[i+1].x - points[i].x, 2) + Math.pow(points[i+1].y - points[i].y, 2)) + 'px';\n                line.style.transform = `rotate(${Math.atan2(points[i+1].y - points[i].y, points[i+1].x - points[i].x)}rad)`;\n                proofGraph.appendChild(line);\n                \n                // Lower bound line\n                const lowerLine = document.createElement('div');\n                lowerLine.className = 'line';\n                lowerLine.style.left = lowerPoints[i].x + 'px';\n                lowerLine.style.top = lowerPoints[i].y + 'px';\n                lowerLine.style.width = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(lowerPoints[i+1].x - lowerPoints[i].x, 2) + Math.pow(lowerPoints[i+1].y - lowerPoints[i].y, 2)) + 'px';\n                lowerLine.style.transform = `rotate(${Math.atan2(lowerPoints[i+1].y - lowerPoints[i].y, lowerPoints[i+1].x - lowerPoints[i].x)}rad)`;\n                lowerLine.style.borderTop = '1px dashed #000';\n                proofGraph.appendChild(lowerLine);\n                \n                // Upper bound line\n                const upperLine = document.createElement('div');\n                upperLine.className = 'line';\n                upperLine.style.left = upperPoints[i].x + 'px';\n                upperLine.style.top = upperPoints[i].y + 'px';\n                upperLine.style.width = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(upperPoints[i+1].x - upperPoints[i].x, 2) + Math.pow(upperPoints[i+1].y - upperPoints[i].y, 2)) + 'px';\n                upperLine.style.transform = `rotate(${Math.atan2(upperPoints[i+1].y - upperPoints[i].y, upperPoints[i+1].x - upperPoints[i].x)}rad)`;\n                upperLine.style.borderTop = '1px dashed #000';\n                proofGraph.appendChild(upperLine);\n            }\n            \n            // Draw n₀ marker\n            const n0X = (n0 / maxN) * proofGraph.clientWidth;\n            const n0Marker = document.createElement('div');\n            n0Marker.className = 'line';\n            n0Marker.style.left = n0X + 'px';\n            n0Marker.style.top = '0';\n            n0Marker.style.width = proofGraph.clientHeight + 'px';\n            n0Marker.style.transform = 'rotate(90deg)';\n            n0Marker.style.backgroundColor = 'red';\n            proofGraph.appendChild(n0Marker);\n            \n            // Check if bounds hold\n            let valid = true;\n            for (let n = n0; n <= maxN; n++) {\n                const fn = evaluateFunction(fExpr, n);\n                const lower = c1 * evaluateFunction(fExpr, n);\n                const upper = c2 * evaluateFunction(fExpr, n);\n                \n                if (fn < lower || fn > upper) {\n                    valid = false;\n                    break;\n                }\n            }\n            \n            proofResult.innerHTML = valid ?\n                `<p>For f(n) = ${getFunctionName(fExpr)}, with c₁ = ${c1}, c₂ = ${c2}, and n₀ = ${n0}, the condition holds. Therefore, f(n) = Θ(${getFunctionName(fExpr)})</p>` :\n                `<p>The condition fails for some n ≥ n₀. Try adjusting the constants or n₀.</p>`;\n        }\n        \n        function autoAdjustConstants() {\n            const fExpr = functionSelect.value;\n            \n            // Simple auto-adjust logic\n            if (fExpr === 'n' || fExpr === 'n^2' || fExpr === 'n^3') {\n                c1Slider.value = 0.5;\n                c2Slider.value = 1.5;\n            } else if (fExpr === 'log n') {\n                c1Slider.value = 0.3;\n                c2Slider.value = 3;\n            } else if (fExpr === 'n log n') {\n                c1Slider.value = 0.7;\n                c2Slider.value = 1.3;\n            } else if (fExpr === '2^n') {\n                c1Slider.value = 0.9;\n                c2Slider.value = 1.1;\n            }\n            \n            n0Slider.value = 5;\n            updateProof();\n        }\n        \n        // Comparison section\n        const compareF1 = document.getElementById('compare-f1');\n        const compareF2 = document.getElementById('compare-f2');\n        const compareMaxN = document.getElementById('compare-max-n');\n        const compareMaxNValue = document.getElementById('compare-max-n-value');\n        const compareBtn = document.getElementById('compare-btn');\n        const compareGraph = document.getElementById('compare-graph');\n        const comparisonResult = document.getElementById('comparison-result');\n        \n        function updateComparison() {\n            const f1 = compareF1.value;\n            const f2 = compareF2.value;\n            const maxN = parseInt(compareMaxN.value);\n            \n            compareMaxNValue.textContent = maxN;\n            \n            // Clear previous graph\n            compareGraph.innerHTML = '';\n            \n            // Calculate points\n            const f1Points = [];\n            const f2Points = [];\n            \n            for (let n = 1; n <= maxN; n++) {\n                const x = (n / maxN) * compareGraph.clientWidth;\n                \n                const f1Y = compareGraph.clientHeight - (evaluateFunction(f1, n) / evaluateFunction(f1, maxN)) * compareGraph.clientHeight;\n                f1Points.push({x, y: f1Y, n});\n                \n                const f2Y = compareGraph.clientHeight - (evaluateFunction(f2, n) / evaluateFunction(f2, maxN)) * compareGraph.clientHeight;\n                f2Points.push({x, y: f2Y, n});\n            }\n            \n            // Draw lines\n            for (let i = 0; i < f1Points.length - 1; i++) {\n                // f1 line\n                const f1Line = document.createElement('div');\n                f1Line.className = 'line';\n                f1Line.style.left = f1Points[i].x + 'px';\n                f1Line.style.top = f1Points[i].y + 'px';\n                f1Line.style.width = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(f1Points[i+1].x - f1Points[i].x, 2) + Math.pow(f1Points[i+1].y - f1Points[i].y, 2)) + 'px';\n                f1Line.style.transform = `rotate(${Math.atan2(f1Points[i+1].y - f1Points[i].y, f1Points[i+1].x - f1Points[i].x)}rad)`;\n                compareGraph.appendChild(f1Line);\n                \n                // f2 line\n                const f2Line = document.createElement('div');\n                f2Line.className = 'line';\n                f2Line.style.left = f2Points[i].x + 'px';\n                f2Line.style.top = f2Points[i].y + 'px';\n                f2Line.style.width = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(f2Points[i+1].x - f2Points[i].x, 2) + Math.pow(f2Points[i+1].y - f2Points[i].y, 2)) + 'px';\n                f2Line.style.transform = `rotate(${Math.atan2(f2Points[i+1].y - f2Points[i].y, f2Points[i+1].x - f2Points[i].x)}rad)`;\n                f2Line.style.borderTop = '1px dashed #000';\n                compareGraph.appendChild(f2Line);\n            }\n            \n            // Determine relationship\n            const f1Name = getFunctionName(f1);\n            const f2Name = getFunctionName(f2);\n            \n            // Simple comparison logic\n            let resultText = '';\n            if (f1 === f2) {\n                resultText = `<p>${f1Name} = Θ(${f2Name}) (they are the same function)</p>`;\n            } else if (\n                (f1 === 'n' && f2 === 'n^2') || \n                (f1 === 'n' && f2 === 'n^3') ||\n                (f1 === 'n^2' && f2 === 'n^3') ||\n                (f1 === 'log n' && (f2 === 'n' || f2 === 'n^2' || f2 === 'n^3')) ||\n                (f1 === 'n log n' && (f2 === 'n^2' || f2 === 'n^3'))\n            ) {\n                resultText = `<p>${f1Name} = O(${f2Name}) but ${f1Name} ≠ Θ(${f2Name}) (${f1Name} grows slower)</p>`;\n            } else if (\n                (f2 === 'n' && f1 === 'n^2') || \n                (f2 === 'n' && f1 === 'n^3') ||\n                (f2 === 'n^2' && f1 === 'n^3') ||\n                (f2 === 'log n' && (f1 === 'n' || f1 === 'n^2' || f1 === 'n^3')) ||\n                (f2 === 'n log n' && (f1 === 'n^2' || f1 === 'n^3'))\n            ) {\n                resultText = `<p>${f2Name} = O(${f1Name}) but ${f1Name} ≠ Θ(${f2Name}) (${f1Name} grows faster)</p>`;\n            } else {\n                resultText = `<p>${f1Name} and ${f2Name} are not asymptotically comparable in simple terms</p>`;\n            }\n            \n            comparisonResult.innerHTML = resultText;\n        }\n        \n        // Algorithm analysis section\n        const algorithmSelect = document.getElementById('algorithm-select');\n        const algorithmN = document.getElementById('algorithm-n');\n        const algorithmNValue = document.getElementById('algorithm-n-value');\n        const analyzeBtn = document.getElementById('analyze-btn');\n        const algorithmResult = document.getElementById('algorithm-result');\n        \n        function analyzeAlgorithm() {\n            const algorithm = algorithmSelect.value;\n            const n = parseInt(algorithmN.value);\n            \n            algorithmNValue.textContent = n;\n            \n            const complexities = {\n                'linear-search': {\n                    theta: 'n',\n                    explanation: 'In the worst case, we need to check every element once.'\n                },\n                'binary-search': {\n                    theta: 'log n',\n                    explanation: 'Each comparison halves the search space.'\n                },\n                'bubble-sort': {\n                    theta: 'n^2',\n                    explanation: 'Nested loops result in n*(n-1)/2 comparisons in worst case.'\n                },\n                'merge-sort': {\n                    theta: 'n log n',\n                    explanation: 'Divide and conquer approach with log n levels, each level doing n work.'\n                },\n                'quick-sort': {\n                    theta: 'n log n',\n                    explanation: 'Average case with good pivot selection (worst case is n²).'\n                },\n                'fibonacci-recursive': {\n                    theta: '2^n',\n                    explanation: 'Exponential growth due to repeated calculations in recursion tree.'\n                }\n            };\n            \n            const info = complexities[algorithm];\n            const table = algorithmResult.querySelector('table');\n            \n            // Clear previous rows\n            while (table.rows.length > 1) {\n                table.deleteRow(1);\n            }\n            \n            const row = table.insertRow();\n            row.insertCell().textContent = algorithm.replace('-', ' ').replace(/\\b\\w/g, l => l.toUpperCase());\n            row.insertCell().textContent = `Θ(${getFunctionName(info.theta)})`;\n            row.insertCell().textContent = info.explanation;\n        }\n        \n        // Custom tester section\n        const customF = document.getElementById('custom-f');\n        const customG = document.getElementById('custom-g');\n        const testBtn = document.getElementById('test-btn');\n        const testResult = document.getElementById('test-result');\n        \n        function testCustomFunctions() {\n            const fExpr = customF.value;\n            const gExpr = customG.value;\n            \n            // Simple test for common cases\n            if (fExpr === gExpr) {\n                testResult.innerHTML = `<p>f(n) = ${fExpr} = Θ(${gExpr}) (same function)</p>`;\n                return;\n            }\n            \n            // Try to find constants\n            let c1, c2, n0;\n            let found = false;\n            \n            // Test for polynomial cases\n            if (fExpr.includes('^') && gExpr.includes('^')) {\n                const fDegree = parseInt(fExpr.split('^')[1]);\n                const gDegree = parseInt(gExpr.split('^')[1]);\n                \n                if (fDegree === gDegree) {\n                    // Same degree, can find constants\n                    c1 = 0.5;\n                    c2 = 2;\n                    n0 = 10;\n                    found = true;\n                }\n            }\n            \n            // Test for log cases\n            if ((fExpr.includes('log') && gExpr.includes('log')) || \n                (fExpr.includes('n log') && gExpr.includes('n log'))) {\n                c1 = 0.5;\n                c2 = 2;\n                n0 = 10;\n                found = true;\n            }\n            \n            if (found) {\n                testResult.innerHTML = `<p>Possible: f(n) = Θ(${gExpr}) with c₁ = ${c1}, c₂ = ${c2}, n₀ = ${n0}</p>`;\n            } else {\n                testResult.innerHTML = `<p>f(n) ≠ Θ(${gExpr}) or more analysis needed (try the proof section)</p>`;\n            }\n        }\n        \n        // Event listeners\n        function setupEventListeners() {\n            // Proof section\n            functionSelect.addEventListener('change', updateProof);\n            c1Slider.addEventListener('input', updateProof);\n            c2Slider.addEventListener('input', updateProof);\n            n0Slider.addEventListener('input', updateProof);\n            autoAdjustBtn.addEventListener('click', autoAdjustConstants);\n            \n            // Comparison section\n            compareF1.addEventListener('change', updateComparison);\n            compareF2.addEventListener('change', updateComparison);\n            compareMaxN.addEventListener('input', updateComparison);\n            compareBtn.addEventListener('click', updateComparison);\n            \n            // Algorithm analysis\n            algorithmSelect.addEventListener('change', analyzeAlgorithm);\n            algorithmN.addEventListener('input', analyzeAlgorithm);\n            analyzeBtn.addEventListener('click', analyzeAlgorithm);\n            \n            // Custom tester\n            testBtn.addEventListener('click', testCustomFunctions);\n        }\n        \n        // Initialize\n        function init() {\n            setupEventListeners();\n            updateProof();\n            updateComparison();\n            analyzeAlgorithm();\n        }\n        \n        window.onload = init;\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
